"{\"opportunities\":[{\"name\":\"Supporting Grassroots Music\",\"organization\":\"Arts Council England\",\"funding\":\"\u00a32.5 million\",\"details\":\"The Supporting Grassroots Music fund is part of the UK Government\u2019s Creative Industries Sector Vision, funded by the Department for Culture, Media and Sport. It specifically supports rehearsal and recording studios, festivals, promoters, and venues for live and electronic music performance. This programme is a time-limited priority within National Lottery Project Grants. An additional ring-fenced budget of \u00a31.5 million is available within Project Grants specifically to support the grassroots live music sector.\",\"eligibility\":\"The fund supports rehearsal and recording studios, festivals, promoters, as well as venues for live and electronic music performance within the grassroots music sector.\",\"application_requirements\":\"Applicants are advised to familiarize themselves with all relevant guidance documents and information sheets before starting their application for this time-limited priority.\",\"other\":\"The programme follows a previous \u00a35 million investment covering November 2023 to April 2025. An evaluation of the Supporting Grassroots Live Music fund (2019-2023) was commissioned to inform the design of this current programme.\"}]}"